My top 6 favourite music videos on YouTube

I love so much about the internet, but sometimes YouTube is about the best thing there is. Obviously not most of it - but anything that means I can watch the following any time I like has to be pretty damn brilliant!

#1 - Obviously... Galaxie 500 playing under a basketball hoop

#2 - Beat Happening playing an in-store outside

#3 Ira and Georgia doing a YouTube thing years before there was YT

#4 Whistling Jack Smith because!

#5 It's James Last and his Orchestra playing Hawkwind's Silver Machine

#6 The Feelies playing Egyptian Reggae in a hotel room
